parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delamination and rusting of the fuel tank can cause fuel leaks, fuel pump failure, and engine stalling, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.

The failure of fuel system components, such as fuel injectors, fuel pumps, and fuel filters, can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and difficulty accelerating, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The malfunction of the fuel gauge can cause inaccurate fuel level readings, leading to fuel starvation, engine stalling, and loss of power, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the accelerator pedal can cause a loss of power, difficulty accelerating, and engine stalling, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
